cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.SY 

This paper deals with the problem of automatic target recognition using RF sensors and synthetic aperture radar signals. This problem is closely related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) as the authors propose to use deep learning techniques to learn robust representations for classification. Additionally, the use of neural networks for classification falls under the category of neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE). The authors also mention the use of adversarial attacks to mask true target characteristics, which is a common problem in the field of adversarial machine learning (cs.AI). Finally, the use of RF sensors for target recognition is also relevant to the field of control systems (cs.SY).
